cs.RO, cs.CG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with path planning for spatial robots amidst obstacles, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The use of subdivision atlases and soft predicates suggests a computational geometry (cs.CG) approach. The algorithms are rigorous and complete, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The practical implementation and comparison with state-of-the-art planners suggest a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the extension of feature-based techniques for collision detection suggests a computer vision (cs.CV) angle.
